4.55/5  rDev +2.2%look: 4.5 | smell: 4.5 | taste: 4.5 | feel: 4.5 |  overall: 4.75Serving: Bottle
Date: Nov-2-2016
A:
Pours a thick pitch black
with a huge cream coffee-and-cream head. Great retention; rings of lacing.
 (4.5)
S:
Smooth blend of coffee, roast malts, vanilla barrel character and some other complimentary bourbon richness.  (4.5)
T:
Smooth as a baby's behind with a cascade of similar flavors to the nose, coffee and cream, maple syrup, vanilla, roast nutty body and a thin bourbon finish. (4.5)
M:
 Rich, full, creamy body with velvety carbonation and a lasting, smooth, warming finish. (4.5)
O:
Wowee! 
Definitely a delicious take on an amazing beer. It pours beautifully to the point that it even has a Macro-lager-commercial-esque head overflow. This is the kind of beer I can point to when people act like a boozy stout shouldn't have a gorgeous head cause of the alcohol. The small and flavor walk hand-in-hand with standard Péché riding on the back of oak vanillins, bourbon sweetness and a mallet sweetness that really makes it all taste like if you put maple, bourbon and cream in espresso and then carbonated it. The feel is fantastic, the flavor and smell as well. Truly a great beer. (4.75) 1,145 charactersTheDoctor, Jun 04, 2015
