4.8/5  rDev +7.9%look: 4.5 | smell: 5 | taste: 4.75 | feel: 4.75 |  overall: 4.75Pours pitch black with a very thin tan head. The nose is deep chocolate fudge, vanilla bean, a bit of dried dark fruit (Glosette raisins almost), some bourbon sweetness, and just a touch of dark roast coffee; extremely well rounded. Taste is full blown dessert; chocolate brownie, espresso, more vanilla, more bourbon, exceedingly delicious. Mouthfeel is fairly thick but silky smooth, light on carbonation, a slight boozy warmth.
Overall, one of my all time favourite stouts. Removes a lot of the roast/bitter characteristic of regular Peche and replaces it with some of the smoothest bourbon and chocolate flavours I've tasted in a beer. What sets this beer apart is not how bold of a flavour it produces but the integration of all of the flavours together; absolutely expertly crafted. 789 charactersBeervana, Mar 18, 2015
